29inline constexpr Condition Negate(Condition cond) {
30 switch (cond) {
31 case kEqual:
32 return kNotEqual;
33 case kNotEqual:
34 return kEqual;
35 case kLessThan:
36 return kGreaterThanEqual;
37 case kLessThanEqual:
38 return kGreaterThan;
39 case kGreaterThanEqual:
40 return kLessThan;
41 case kGreaterThan:
42 return kLessThanEqual;
43 case kUnsignedLessThan:
44 return kUnsignedGreaterThanEqual;
45 case kUnsignedLessThanEqual:
46 return kUnsignedGreaterThan;
47 case kUnsignedGreaterThanEqual:
48 return kUnsignedLessThan;
49 case kUnsignedGreaterThan:
50 return kUnsignedLessThanEqual;
51 default:
52 UNREACHABLE();
53 }
54}
55
56inline constexpr Condition Flip(Condition cond) {
57 switch (cond) {
58 case kEqual:
59 return kEqual;
60 case kNotEqual:
61 return kNotEqual;
62 case kLessThan:
63 return kGreaterThan;
64 case kLessThanEqual:
65 return kGreaterThanEqual;
66 case kGreaterThanEqual:
67 return kLessThanEqual;
68 case kGreaterThan:
69 return kLessThan;
70 case kUnsignedLessThan:
71 return kUnsignedGreaterThan;
72 case kUnsignedLessThanEqual:
73 return kUnsignedGreaterThanEqual;
74 case kUnsignedGreaterThanEqual:
75 return kUnsignedLessThanEqual;
76 case kUnsignedGreaterThan:
77 return kUnsignedLessThan;
78 default:
79 UNREACHABLE();
80 }
81}

154 bool has_unused_register(RegClass rc, LiftoffRegList pinned = {}) const {
155 if (kNeedI64RegPair && rc == kGpRegPair) {
156 LiftoffRegList available_regs =
157 kGpCacheRegList.MaskOut(used_registers).MaskOut(pinned);
158 return available_regs.GetNumRegsSet() >= 2;
159 } else if (kNeedS128RegPair && rc == kFpRegPair) {
160 LiftoffRegList available_regs =
161 kFpCacheRegList.MaskOut(used_registers).MaskOut(pinned);
162 return available_regs.HasAdjacentFpRegsSet();
163 }
164 LiftoffRegList candidates = GetCacheRegList(rc);
165 return has_unused_register(candidates.MaskOut(pinned));
166 }
167
168 bool has_unused_register(LiftoffRegList candidates) const {
169 LiftoffRegList available_regs = candidates.MaskOut(used_registers);
170 return !available_regs.is_empty();
171 }
172
173 LiftoffRegister unused_register(RegClass rc,
174 LiftoffRegList pinned = {}) const {
175 if (kNeedI64RegPair && rc == kGpRegPair) {
176 Register low = pinned.set(unused_register(kGpReg, pinned)).gp();
177 Register high = unused_register(kGpReg, pinned).gp();
178 return LiftoffRegister::ForPair(low, high);
179 } else if (kNeedS128RegPair && rc == kFpRegPair) {
180 LiftoffRegList available_regs =
181 kFpCacheRegList.MaskOut(used_registers).MaskOut(pinned);
182 DoubleRegister low =
183 available_regs.GetAdjacentFpRegsSet().GetFirstRegSet().fp();
184 DCHECK(is_free(LiftoffRegister::ForFpPair(low)));
185 return LiftoffRegister::ForFpPair(low);
186 }
187 LiftoffRegList candidates = GetCacheRegList(rc);
188 return unused_register(candidates, pinned);
189 }
190
191 LiftoffRegister unused_register(LiftoffRegList candidates,
192 LiftoffRegList pinned = {}) const {
193 LiftoffRegList available_regs =
194 candidates.MaskOut(used_registers).MaskOut(pinned);
195 return available_regs.GetFirstRegSet();
196 }
197
198 // Volatile registers are registers which are used for caching values that
199 // can easily be reloaded. Those are returned first if we run out of free
200 // registers.
201 bool has_volatile_register(LiftoffRegList candidates) {
202 return (cached_instance_data != no_reg &&
203 candidates.has(cached_instance_data)) ||
204 (cached_mem_start != no_reg && candidates.has(cached_mem_start));
205 }
206
207 LiftoffRegister take_volatile_register(LiftoffRegList candidates) {
208 DCHECK(!frozen);
209 DCHECK(has_volatile_register(candidates));
210 Register reg = no_reg;
211 if (cached_instance_data != no_reg &&
212 candidates.has(cached_instance_data)) {
213 reg = cached_instance_data;
214 cached_instance_data = no_reg;
215 } else {
216 DCHECK(candidates.has(cached_mem_start));
217 reg = cached_mem_start;
218 cached_mem_start = no_reg;
219 cached_mem_index = kNoCachedMemIndex;
220 }
221
222 LiftoffRegister ret{reg};
223 DCHECK_EQ(1, register_use_count[ret.liftoff_code()]);
224 register_use_count[ret.liftoff_code()] = 0;
225 used_registers.clear(ret);
226 return ret;
227 }
228
229 void SetCacheRegister(Register* cache, Register reg) {
230 DCHECK(!frozen);
231 DCHECK_EQ(no_reg, *cache);
232 *cache = reg;
233 int liftoff_code = LiftoffRegister{reg}.liftoff_code();
234 DCHECK_EQ(0, register_use_count[liftoff_code]);
235 register_use_count[liftoff_code] = 1;
236 used_registers.set(reg);
237 }

239 void SetInstanceCacheRegister(Register reg) {
240 SetCacheRegister(&cached_instance_data, reg);
241 }
242
243 void SetMemStartCacheRegister(Register reg, int memory_index) {
244 SetCacheRegister(&cached_mem_start, reg);
245 DCHECK_EQ(kNoCachedMemIndex, cached_mem_index);
246 cached_mem_index = memory_index;
247 }

249 Register TrySetCachedInstanceRegister(LiftoffRegList pinned) {
250 DCHECK_EQ(no_reg, cached_instance_data);
251 LiftoffRegList available_regs =
252 kGpCacheRegList.MaskOut(pinned).MaskOut(used_registers);
253 if (available_regs.is_empty()) return no_reg;
254 // Prefer the {kWasmInstanceRegister}, because that's where the instance
255 // initially is, and where it needs to be for calls.
256 Register new_cache_reg = available_regs.has(kWasmInstanceRegister)
257 ? kWasmInstanceRegister
258 : available_regs.GetFirstRegSet().gp();
259 SetInstanceCacheRegister(new_cache_reg);
260 DCHECK_EQ(new_cache_reg, cached_instance_data);
261 return new_cache_reg;
262 }

264 V8_INLINE void ClearCacheRegister(Register* cache) {
265 DCHECK(!frozen);
266 V8_ASSUME(cache == &cached_instance_data || cache == &cached_mem_start);
267 if (*cache == no_reg) return;
268 int liftoff_code = LiftoffRegister{*cache}.liftoff_code();
269 DCHECK_EQ(1, register_use_count[liftoff_code]);
270 register_use_count[liftoff_code] = 0;
271 used_registers.clear(*cache);
272 *cache = no_reg;
273 }

275 void ClearCachedInstanceRegister() {
276 ClearCacheRegister(&cached_instance_data);
277 }

279 void ClearCachedMemStartRegister() {
280 V8_ASSUME(cached_mem_index == kNoCachedMemIndex || cached_mem_index >= 0);
281 if (cached_mem_index == kNoCachedMemIndex) return;
282 cached_mem_index = kNoCachedMemIndex;
283 DCHECK_NE(no_reg, cached_mem_start);
284 ClearCacheRegister(&cached_mem_start);
285 }

292 void inc_used(LiftoffRegister reg) {
293 DCHECK(!frozen);
294 if (reg.is_pair()) {
295 inc_used(reg.low());
296 inc_used(reg.high());
297 return;
298 }
299 used_registers.set(reg);
300 DCHECK_GT(kMaxInt, register_use_count[reg.liftoff_code()]);
301 ++register_use_count[reg.liftoff_code()];
302 }
303
304 // Returns whether this was the last use.
305 void dec_used(LiftoffRegister reg) {
306 DCHECK(!frozen);
307 DCHECK(is_used(reg));
308 if (reg.is_pair()) {
309 dec_used(reg.low());
310 dec_used(reg.high());
311 return;
312 }
313 int code = reg.liftoff_code();
314 DCHECK_LT(0, register_use_count[code]);
315 if (--register_use_count[code] == 0) used_registers.clear(reg);
316 }
317
318 bool is_used(LiftoffRegister reg) const {
319 if (reg.is_pair()) return is_used(reg.low()) || is_used(reg.high());
320 bool used = used_registers.has(reg);
321 DCHECK_EQ(used, register_use_count[reg.liftoff_code()] != 0);
322 return used;
323 }
324
325 uint32_t get_use_count(LiftoffRegister reg) const {
326 if (reg.is_pair()) {
327 DCHECK_EQ(register_use_count[reg.low().liftoff_code()],
328 register_use_count[reg.high().liftoff_code()]);
329 reg = reg.low();
330 }
331 DCHECK_GT(arraysize(register_use_count), reg.liftoff_code());
332 return register_use_count[reg.liftoff_code()];
333 }
334
335 void clear_used(LiftoffRegister reg) {
336 DCHECK(!frozen);
337 if (reg.is_pair()) {
338 clear_used(reg.low());
339 clear_used(reg.high());
340 return;
341 }
342 register_use_count[reg.liftoff_code()] = 0;
343 used_registers.clear(reg);
344 }
345
346 bool is_free(LiftoffRegister reg) const { return !is_used(reg); }
347
348 void reset_used_registers() {
349 DCHECK(!frozen);
350 used_registers = {};
351 memset(register_use_count, 0, sizeof(register_use_count));
352 }

354 LiftoffRegister GetNextSpillReg(LiftoffRegList candidates) {
355 DCHECK(!frozen);
356 DCHECK(!candidates.is_empty());
357 // This method should only be called if none of the candidates is free.
358 DCHECK(candidates.MaskOut(used_registers).is_empty());
359 LiftoffRegList unspilled = candidates.MaskOut(last_spilled_regs);
360 if (unspilled.is_empty()) {
361 unspilled = candidates;
362 last_spilled_regs = {};
363 }
364 LiftoffRegister reg = unspilled.GetFirstRegSet();
365 return reg;
366 }

386 // Load a cache slot to a free register.
387 V8_INLINE LiftoffRegister LoadToRegister(VarState slot,
388 LiftoffRegList pinned) {
389 if (V8_LIKELY(slot.is_reg())) return slot.reg();
390 return LoadToRegister_Slow(slot, pinned);
391 }

397 // Load a non-register cache slot to a given (fixed) register.
398 inline void LoadToFixedRegister(VarState slot, LiftoffRegister reg);
399
400 // Load a cache slot to a register that has no other uses, so it can be
401 // modified.
402 LiftoffRegister LoadToModifiableRegister(VarState slot,
403 LiftoffRegList pinned) {
404 LiftoffRegister reg = LoadToRegister(slot, pinned);
405 // TODO(jkummerow): The following line is overly optimistic, as long as
406 // we don't pop the VarState, the register will never be considered free.
407 if (cache_state()->is_free(reg) && !pinned.has(reg)) return reg;
408
409 LiftoffRegister new_reg = GetUnusedRegister(reg.reg_class(), pinned);
410 // {new_reg} could be equal to {reg}, but it's unused by the stack now.
411 // Also, {reg} still holds the previous value, even if it was spilled.
412 if (new_reg != reg) Move(new_reg, reg, slot.kind());
413 return new_reg;
414 }
415
416 // Pop a VarState from the stack, updating the register use count accordingly.
417 V8_INLINE VarState PopVarState() {
418 DCHECK(!cache_state_.stack_state.empty());
419 VarState slot = cache_state_.stack_state.back();
420 cache_state_.stack_state.pop_back();
421 if (V8_LIKELY(slot.is_reg())) cache_state_.dec_used(slot.reg());
422 return slot;
423 }
424
425 V8_INLINE LiftoffRegister PopToRegister(LiftoffRegList pinned = {}) {
426 VarState slot = PopVarState();
427 return LoadToRegister(slot, pinned);
428 }

432 // Use this to pop a value into a register that has no other uses, so it
433 // can be modified.
434 LiftoffRegister PopToModifiableRegister(LiftoffRegList pinned = {}) {
435 ValueKind kind = cache_state_.stack_state.back().kind();
436 LiftoffRegister reg = PopToRegister(pinned);
437 if (cache_state()->is_free(reg) && !pinned.has(reg)) return reg;
438
439 LiftoffRegister new_reg = GetUnusedRegister(reg.reg_class(), pinned);
440 // {new_reg} could be equal to {reg}, but it's unused by the stack now.
441 // Also, {reg} still holds the previous value, even if it was spilled.
442 if (new_reg != reg) Move(new_reg, reg, kind);
443 return new_reg;
444 }

446 // Returns the register which holds the value of stack slot {index}. If the
447 // value is not stored in a register yet, a register is allocated for it. The

487 // Get an unused register for class {rc}, reusing one of {try_first} if
488 // possible.
489 LiftoffRegister GetUnusedRegister(
490 RegClass rc, std::initializer_list<LiftoffRegister> try_first,
491 LiftoffRegList pinned) {
492 DCHECK(!cache_state_.frozen);
493 for (LiftoffRegister reg : try_first) {
494 DCHECK_EQ(reg.reg_class(), rc);
495 if (cache_state_.is_free(reg)) return reg;
496 }
497 return GetUnusedRegister(rc, pinned);
498 }
499
500 // Get an unused register for class {rc}, excluding registers from {pinned},
501 // potentially spilling to free one.
502 LiftoffRegister GetUnusedRegister(RegClass rc, LiftoffRegList pinned) {
503 DCHECK(!cache_state_.frozen);
504 if (kNeedI64RegPair && rc == kGpRegPair) {
505 LiftoffRegList candidates = kGpCacheRegList.MaskOut(pinned);
506 Register low = candidates.clear(GetUnusedRegister(candidates)).gp();
507 Register high = GetUnusedRegister(candidates).gp();
508 return LiftoffRegister::ForPair(low, high);
509 } else if (kNeedS128RegPair && rc == kFpRegPair) {
510 // kFpRegPair specific logic here because we need adjacent registers, not
511 // just any two registers (like kGpRegPair).
512 if (cache_state_.has_unused_register(rc, pinned)) {
513 return cache_state_.unused_register(rc, pinned);
514 }
515 DoubleRegister low_fp = SpillAdjacentFpRegisters(pinned).fp();
516 return LiftoffRegister::ForFpPair(low_fp);
517 }
518 LiftoffRegList candidates = GetCacheRegList(rc).MaskOut(pinned);
519 return GetUnusedRegister(candidates);
520 }
521
522 // Get an unused register of {candidates}, potentially spilling to free one.
523 LiftoffRegister GetUnusedRegister(LiftoffRegList candidates) {
524 DCHECK(!cache_state_.frozen);
525 DCHECK(!candidates.is_empty());
526 if (V8_LIKELY(cache_state_.has_unused_register(candidates))) {
527 return cache_state_.unused_register(candidates);
528 }
529 return SpillOneRegister(candidates);
530 }

553 // Clear any uses of {reg} in both the cache and in {possible_uses}.

561 // Spills all passed registers.
562 template <typename... Regs>
563 void SpillRegisters(Regs... regs) {
564 for (LiftoffRegister r : {LiftoffRegister(regs)...}) {
565 if (cache_state_.is_free(r)) continue;
566 if (r.is_gp() && cache_state_.cached_instance_data == r.gp()) {
567 cache_state_.ClearCachedInstanceRegister();
568 } else if (r.is_gp() && cache_state_.cached_mem_start == r.gp()) {
569 V8_ASSUME(cache_state_.cached_mem_index >= 0);
570 cache_state_.ClearCachedMemStartRegister();
571 } else {
572 SpillRegister(r);
573 }
574 }
575 }
